script4_EnrichR_Treatment_TAPbyQNP

Shradha Mukherjee

Last updated January, 2019

  1. This pipeline does a global miRNA target scan using enrichR as follows:
  1. miRNAs target analysis (not just miR142 but other miRNAs too), using “TargetScan_microRNA_2017”, “miRTarBase_2017”,
  2. Gene ontology “GO_Biological_Process_2018”.
  3. Pathway analysis “KEGG_2018”
  4. Curated “OMIM_Disease”, “OMIM_Expanded”, all diseases
  5. Tissue type enrichment form human “Human_Gene_Atlas” and mouse “Mouse_Gene_Atlas”,
  6. Potential drugs that can target the module genes “DrugMatrix” and “DSigDB” .
  7. Transcription factor regulation “ChEA 2016” and “ENCODE TF ChIP-seq 2015”
  8. Epigenetic regulation “Epigenomics Roadmap HM ChIP-seq” and “ENCODE Histone Modifications 2015”
  9. cancer cell lines “Cancer Cell Line Encyclopedia” and “NCI-60 Cancer Cell Lines”

2)To use this code for different DEG list of genes change the genes in mygenes

#Import new DEG data we got from our analysis containing genes
load(file="./DEG_AllDEGmethods_results/DEG_AllDEGmethodsnames.RData")
#DEG_AllDEGmethodsnames=as.data.frame(DEG_AllDEGmethodsnames)
mygenes=c(DEG_AllDEGmethodsnames[,1],DEG_AllDEGmethodsnames[,2], DEG_AllDEGmethodsnames[,3],DEG_AllDEGmethodsnames[,4])
mygenes=as.data.frame(mygenes)
mygenes$Category="TAPbyQNP"
colnames(mygenes)=c("Gene", "Category")
mygenes=mygenes[!duplicated(mygenes$Gene),]
